@startuml
title JavaWatch - Coffee Bean Replenishment System Control Flow

actor User
participant "Website\n(registration.html)" as Website
participant "Amazon Login" as AmazonLogin
participant "Raspberry Pi\n(photo.py)" as RaspberryPi
participant "Camera" as Camera
participant "S3 Bucket" as S3
participant "Lambda\n(checkImage.py)" as CheckImageLambda
participant "Amazon Rekognition" as Rekognition
participant "Lambda\n(labelCheck.js)" as LabelCheckLambda
participant "Amazon DRS" as DRS

== Device Registration ==
User -> Website: Access registration page
activate Website
Website -> User: Display registration form\n(Product Model ID, Serial Number)
deactivate Website

User -> Website: Submit registration details
activate Website
Website -> AmazonLogin: Initiate "Login with Amazon"
activate AmazonLogin
AmazonLogin -> User: Request authentication
User -> AmazonLogin: Provide credentials
AmazonLogin -> Website: Return authentication token
deactivate AmazonLogin
Website -> DRS: Link device and user account
activate DRS
DRS -> Website: Confirm registration
deactivate DRS
Website -> User: Display confirmation
deactivate Website

== Image Capture and Upload ==
RaspberryPi -> Camera: Capture image
activate Camera
Camera -> RaspberryPi: Return image data
deactivate Camera

RaspberryPi -> RaspberryPi: Overlay timestamp on image
RaspberryPi -> S3: Upload image
activate S3
S3 -> RaspberryPi: Confirm upload
deactivate S3

== Image Analysis and Bean Level Detection ==
S3 -> CheckImageLambda: Trigger function (S3 event)
activate CheckImageLambda
CheckImageLambda -> S3: Retrieve image
activate S3
S3 -> CheckImageLambda: Return image data
deactivate S3

CheckImageLambda -> Rekognition: Call detect_labels API
activate Rekognition
Rekognition -> Rekognition: Analyze image
Rekognition -> CheckImageLambda: Return detected labels
deactivate Rekognition

CheckImageLambda -> LabelCheckLambda: Send labels for verification
activate LabelCheckLambda
LabelCheckLambda -> LabelCheckLambda: Check for "Bean" label
deactivate LabelCheckLambda

alt Bean label detected and level is low
    CheckImageLambda -> CheckImageLambda: Determine low bean level
    CheckImageLambda -> DRS: Place replenishment order
    activate DRS
    DRS -> DRS: Process order
    DRS -> CheckImageLambda: Confirm order placed
    deactivate DRS
    CheckImageLambda -> User: Send notification (order placed)
else Bean level sufficient or not detected
    CheckImageLambda -> CheckImageLambda: Log result (no action needed)
end

deactivate CheckImageLambda

@enduml
